ENTRY            A1502   20260317   20260508   20260508       A133
SUBENT        A1502001   20260317   20260508   20260508       A133
BIB                  9         31
TITLE      Accelerator production of 8B neutrinos
AUTHOR     (R.E.Marrs,D.Bodansky,E.G.Adelberger)
REFERENCE  (J,PR/C,8,427,1973)
INSTITUTE  (1USAWAS)
FACILITY   (VDGT,1USAWAS)
SAMPLE     The thick targets of enriched 6Li metal were prepared
           in an argon atmosphere by pressing 6Li metal into a
           small aluminum boat and covering the front surface with
           a 0.025-mm Havar foil. Three targets were 2.5 mm thick.
DETECTOR   (GELI)
ERR-ANALYS   These uncertainties have been combined to obtain a
           final systematic probable error of about 12% at low
           energies and 9% at high energies.
           (ERR-1) Uncertainty in the quoted 22Na source
                                              strength, 4.6%;
           (ERR-2) Uncertainty in the efficiency calibration
                                              procedure, 3%;
           (ERR-3) Uncertainty in the positron annihilation-in-
                                           flight correction, 3%.
           (ERR-4) Uncertainty in the procedure for extraction of
                   the 8B activity by least-squares fitting, 3%;
           (ERR-5,5.,9.) Uncertainty in the beam current
                   integration ranging from 5% to 9%;
           (ERR-S) Statistical error
HISTORY    (19820503C) Compilation produced by RFNC-VNIIEF Sarov
           (19990323U)CNPD: corrected 4-dig. year and lower cases.
           (20110819A) SD: ref. volume changed:  1 -> 8.
           Titles of digitizing errors changed according to Dict.
           ERR-ANALYS was updated. Data were digitized once more.
           (20260317A) SD: Small corrections in all Subents.
           ERR-ANALYS updated in Subent 001.
